## 1  Overview
Tools are modular, async components that our agents can call to perform work (create files, search data catalog, fetch weather, etc.).  Each tool is **transport-agnostic** and communicates with the outside world through three Rust traits:

| Trait | Purpose |






|-------|---------|
| `ToolExecutor`          | Core, synchronous business logic (executes once full parameters are available). |
| `StreamingToolExecutor` | Optional incremental ingestion of LLM token chunks + deferred `finalize()`. |
| `ToolStreamer`          | Optional mapper that converts low-level `StreamStage`s into **UI-ready** events and pushes them to a Tokio channel. |

All three live in `libs/agentsv2/src/tools/tool.rs` and are available everywhere in the workspace.

---

## 2  Quick-Start Template
```rust
use agentsv2::tools::tool::*;
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};

#[derive(Deserialize)]
struct MyParams {
    #[stream(visible, chunk = "query_chunk", full = "query")]
    query: String,
}

#[derive(Serialize)]
struct MyOutput { answer: String }

pub const MY_TOOL: ToolName = ToolName::new("my_tool");

pub struct MyTool { buffer: String, params: Option<MyParams> }

#[async_trait]
impl ToolExecutor for MyTool {
    type Params = MyParams;
    type Output = MyOutput;

    async fn execute(&self, p: Self::Params, _id: String) -> Result<Self::Output> {
        // тАж your business logic тАж
        Ok(MyOutput { answer: format!("Echo: {}", p.query) })
    }

    async fn schema(&self) -> Value { /* produce JSON schema */ }
    fn name(&self) -> ToolName { MY_TOOL }
}

// Derive StreamSpec manually or with the macro (coming soon)
impl StreamSpec for MyParams {
    fn stream_fields() -> &'static [FieldSpec] {
        &[FieldSpec { json_key: "query", ui_chunk_key: Some("query_chunk"), ui_full_key: Some("query") }]
    }
}

// тАФтАФ inherit default StreamingToolExecutor impl by writing your own or using the helper pattern тАФтАФ
```

